# Mintlify MDX (Autex Knowledge Base)

You write and edit Mintlify MDX in this repo. Follow [Mintlify docs](https://mintlify.com/docs) for components; this rule adds Autex conventions.

## Writing

- Second person, active voice, present tense for instructions.
- Lead with outcome; put prerequisites before steps.
- Body headings start at `##` (H2). Use `title` and `description` in frontmatter only for page metadata.
- Use DriveWorks product terms: **Group**, **Project**, **Specification**, **Rule**, **custom function**, **Project document**, **Specification Macro**, **DriveWorks Administrator**.

## Page frontmatter

Every `.mdx` page needs at least:

```yaml
---
title: Clear page title
description: One sentence on purpose and audience
---
```

Optional: `sidebarTitle`, `icon` (Lucide name), `mode` (`wide`, `center`, `frame`, `custom`).

## Navigation

- Register every new page in `docs.json` under the correct tab and group.
- Internal links: absolute paths without extension, e.g. `/driveworks/how-to/sql`.
- After moving or renaming pages, update `docs.json` and inbound links.

## Component selection

| Need                        | Use                                           |
| --------------------------- | --------------------------------------------- |
| Procedure                   | `<Steps>` with `##` step titles               |
| Platform or variant         | `<Tabs>`                                      |
| Prerequisite / context      | `<Info>`                                      |
| Best practice               | `<Tip>`                                       |
| Destructive or risky action | `<Warning>`                                   |
| Supplementary detail        | `<Note>`                                      |
| Success checkpoint          | `<Check>`                                     |
| Hub / related links         | `<CardGroup>` + `<Card>` or `SectionCardGrid` |
| Flow or structure           | Mermaid fenced block                          |
| Optional depth              | `<Accordion>` / `<Expandable>`                |
| Multi-language code         | `<CodeGroup>`                                 |

Prefer Markdown lists and tables when a component adds no clarity.

## Images and media

- Host under project root (e.g. `/images/wiki/...`).
- Wrap screenshots in `<Frame>` with descriptive alt text.

## Custom React (`/snippets/`)

- Named exports only; no default exports.
- Hooks (`useState`, `useEffect`, `useMemo`, etc.) are pre-injected — do not import React hooks.
- No npm packages, no cross-snippet imports, no `.json` imports. Use `.js` modules for data.
- Import every dependency from the parent MDX: `import { Foo } from "/snippets/Foo.jsx"`.
- Tailwind + `not-prose` on custom layout blocks.
- Defer heavy components behind a button or `IntersectionObserver` (no `React.lazy`).

Existing snippets: `DriveWorksRule`, `CustomFunctionDoc`, `SectionCardGrid`, `ArchitectureLayerTable`, diagram components under `snippets/diagrams/`.

## Custom function documentation

- Rule Builder examples: fenced `driveworks` block or `<DriveWorksRule>` / `<CustomFunctionDoc example="...">`.
- One primary call per section; compact formatting (no spaces after commas).
- Realistic symbols: `DWLookup…`, `DWVariable…`, `DWConstant…` where appropriate.
- Do not add UDF example blocks for Specification Flow tasks or Project document types only.

## Errors to avoid

- Wiki.js patterns: `{.tabset}`, `{.is-info}`, sibling `folder.md` routing.
- Forgetting `docs.json` entry for new pages.
- H1 (`#`) in page body (use `##`).
- Link text like "click here".
- Secrets or real credentials in code samples.

## Local workflow

- Preview: `mintlify dev` from repo root.
- Editor: [Mintlify MDX](https://marketplace.visualstudio.com/items?itemName=mintlify.mintlify-snippets) extension for component snippets.
- Mintlify component reference: https://mintlify.com/docs/components
